# !REMARKS:  
#  Customize the unit tests for your system by specifying these values:
#  -------------------------------------------------------------------
#  VERSION     : A tag used to identify this Unit Test (e.g. v9-02o)
#  DESCRIPTION : A short description of what this unit test is validating
#  CODE_DIR    : Full path of the GEOS-Chem code directory
#  DATA_ROOT   : Root GEOS-Chem data directory
#  HEMCO_ROOT  : Root directory where HEMCO emissions data files are stored
#  RUN_ROOT    : Unit test run directories are subdirectories of RUN_ROOT
#  RUN_DIR     : Individual unit test run directory path
#  JOB_DIR     : Unit Test job script directory
#  LOG_DIR     : Unit Test log file directory
#  PERL_DIR    : Unit Test perl script directory (i.e. this directory)
#  VERBOSE     : HEMCO debug output level (0=no output, 3=max output)
#  WARNINGS    : HEMCO warnings output level (0=no warnings, 3=max warnings)
#  COMPILER    : Compiler used to build GEOS-Chem (e.g. "ifort", "pgi")
#  MAKE_CMD    : Make command with basic debugging flags
#  SUBMIT      : Submit command and queue name
#  TEMPLATE    : Template web page for displaying grid of results
#  WEB_GRID    : File name for web page containing unit test results
#  WEB_PUSH    : Remote location to send web page w/ unit test results
#
# !REMARKS:
#  This file specifies unit tests for 2x2.5 resolution.
#  To omit individual unit tests, place a # in the first column.
#
